"He C.-Y., Zhang J.-G., Duan A.-G., Sun H.-G., Fu L.-H., Zheng S.-X.","Proteins responding to drought and high-temperature stress in Pinus armandii Franch",2007,"Canadian Journal of Botany","85","10",,"994","1002",,,10.1139/B07-085,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-39649093923&partnerID=40&md5=16acc04bacadf908c2b2f8da9e109268","Key Laboratory of Silviculture of the State Forestry Administration, Research Institute of Forestry, Chinese Academy of Forestry, Beijing 100091, China","He, C.-Y., Key Laboratory of Silviculture of the State Forestry Administration, Research Institute of Forestry, Chinese Academy of Forestry, Beijing 100091, China; Zhang, J.-G., Key Laboratory of Silviculture of the State Forestry Administration, Research Institute of Forestry, Chinese Academy of Forestry, Beijing 100091, China; Duan, A.-G., Key Laboratory of Silviculture of the State Forestry Administration, Research Institute of Forestry, Chinese Academy of Forestry, Beijing 100091, China; Sun, H.-G., Key Laboratory of Silviculture of the State Forestry Administration, Research Institute of Forestry, Chinese Academy of Forestry, Beijing 100091, China; Fu, L.-H., Key Laboratory of Silviculture of the State Forestry Administration, Research Institute of Forestry, Chinese Academy of Forestry, Beijing 100091, China; Zheng, S.-X., Key Laboratory of Silviculture of the State Forestry Administration, Research Institute of Forestry, Chinese Academy of Forestry, Beijing 100091, China","Proteomic analysis provides a powerful method for studying plant responses to stress at the protein level. To study stress-responsive molecular mechanisms for Pinus armandii Franch, one of the most important forest plantation tree species in subalpine regions of Asia, we analyzed the response of 2-year-old P. armandii seedlings to drought and high temperature using two-dimensional gel electrophoresis. More than 550 reproducible needle proteins were detected in the controls and treatments, and the abundance of 27 proteins were found to change noticeably. We identified five proteins affected by drought stress and eight proteins affected by high temperature. These proteins are functionally quite diverse and are involved in photosynthesis, cell division and elongation, antioxidant metabolism, ammonia assimilation, growth and development, and protein folding. Our results provide fundamental data for future research on responses to drought and high temperature. As drought and high temperature are two major factors limiting the growth of subalpine forests during summer under recent global warming, this research may contribute to an understanding of the development of stress tolerance in trees. © 2007 NRC.","Drought; High temperature; Pinus armandii Franch; Proteomics","Drought; Global warming; Growth kinetics; High temperature effects; High temperature; Pinus armandii Franch; Proteomics; Plants (botany); antioxidant; coniferous tree; drought stress; electrokinesis; global warming; growth rate; high temperature; metabolism; molecular analysis; photosynthesis; plantation forestry; protein; proteomics; seedling emergence; subalpine environment; Asia; Eurasia; Pinus armandii",,,,,,"Ali, G., Srivastava, P.S., Iqbal, M., Proline accumulation, protein pattern and photosynthesis in regenerants grown under NaCl stress (1999) Biol. Plant, 42, pp. 89-95. , doi:10.1023/A:1002127711432; Bahrman, N., Zivy, M., Baradat, P., Damerval, C., Organization of the variability of abundant proteins in seven geographical origins of maritime pine (Pinus pinaster Ait.) (1994) Theor. Appl. Genet, 88, pp. 407-411; Berteli, F., Corrales, E., Guerrero, C., Ariza, M.J., Pliego, F., Valpuesta, V., Salt stress increases ferredoxin-dependent glutamate synthase activity and protein level in the leaves of tomato (1995) Physiol. Plant, 93, pp. 259-264. , doi:10.1111/j.1399-3054.1995.tb02226.x; Bhadula, S.K., Elthon, T.E., Habben, J.E., Helentfaris, T.G., Jiao, S., Ristic, Z., Heat-stress induced synthesi